  "text": "Since N-terminal mutations of FOXO1 in DLBCL are linked to its increased transcriptional activity, [CITATION_1] we analyzed the expression of MS4A1 mRNA in primary FOXO1-wild type and FOXO1-mutated lymphoma samples (ICGC, MALY-DE project). We found that the levels of MS4A1 mRNA in FOXO1-mutated samples (M1V, R21C, R21H, T24A and T24I mutations) were significantly lower than in wild-type FOXO1 samples (averaged normalized expression 1699 versus 2871, respectively, Fig. 5A ).",
